5000|$|While {{there are}} many {{potential}} definitions of domestic terrorism, it is largely defined as terrorism in which the perpetrator targets his/her own country. Enders defines domestic terrorism as “homegrown in which the venue, target, and perpetrators are all from the same country. The term “homegrown terrorism” stems from jihadi terrorism against Westerners. Wilner and Dobouloz described <b>homegrown</b> <b>terrorism</b> as [...] "autonomously organized radicalized Westerners with little direct assistance from transnational networks, usually organized within the home or host country, and targets fellow nationals." [...] However, <b>homegrown</b> <b>terrorism</b> is not just jihad or Islamic.|$|E
