50|$|Five Muslim Americans with {{suspected}} ties {{to terrorism}} were detained on December 9, 2009, in Pakistan. The five men, {{part of an}} increasing trend in <b>homegrown</b> <b>terrorism,</b> {{in their late teens}} to early twenties and from the Washington, D.C., suburbs, were detained during a police raid on a house with links to a militant group. The group is sometimes referred to as the D.C. 5 due to having lived in the D.C. Metro area.|$|E
